## Troubleshooting

### Error: "Access Denied" or "Insufficient Permissions"
- **Solution:** Ensure your account has the **Intune Administrator** role or higher
- Contact your Azure AD administrator if needed

### Error: "Module Not Found"
- **Solution:** The script will attempt to install it automatically. If it fails, manually install:
  ```powershell
  Install-Module -Name Microsoft.Graph.DeviceManagement -Force -AllowClobber
  ```

### Error: "Script execution disabled on this system"
- **Solution:** Run this command:
  ```powershell
  Set-ExecutionPolicy -ExecutionPolicy RemoteSigned -Scope CurrentUser
  ```

### Browser doesn't open for authentication
- **Solution:** Check if your system has internet connectivity
- Ensure no firewall is blocking the connection
- Try running PowerShell in a different network context

### No devices are returned
- **Possible cause:** You have no managed devices in Intune
- **Possible cause:** All devices have synced within the last 90 days

